Senior students and Families,

As you know by now we are having our actual graduation on Tuesday, June 9th at 830pm, at the Goodyear Ballpark.

Seniors, please plan on attending by 7pm in your cap and gown. Masks are recommended. Please report to center field, which can be accessed from the east side of the stadium on Wood Blvd.

Each graduate will be give 5 tickets for their families to attend. Those tickets can be picked up at the Youngker Admin building, beginning Wednesday from 8a-2p. You will need to sign a waiver for them.

If you have questions, please donâ€™t hesitate to call.

#GoRoughriders

Students and Parents: Next week you will be able to turn in all electronics and class materials to campus. We will be available, Tuesday through Friday, 8am-3pm collecting materials.
These items include:
Laptops (PAC)
Athletic uniforms or equipment (Big Gym Lobby)
Class books or materials

All debts on student accounts can be taken care of by calling the bookstore. No diplomas will he mailed until those debts are paid. Seniors received emails today notifying them IF they have a debt.

You can also pick up your yearbooks on Tuesday.

Laptops for seniors will be cleaned and updated and be made available for pickup in the beginning of July. All underclassman, your laptops will be cleaned and updated and picked up at registration in July.

If you have questions, donâ€™t hesitate to ask.

Go Roughriders!

Buckeye AZ Police Department
May 1 at 8:00 AM Â·

Today we remember Buckeye Police Officer Rolando Tirado. When he was killed in the line of duty on May 1, 2011, we made a promise to "Never forget." We have not. Always in our thoughts and in our hearts. Thank you, sir, for your service.
text:
We will never forget

Buckeye AZ Police Department
May 1 at 8:00 AM Â·

Today we remember Buckeye Police Officer Rolando Tirado. When he was killed in the line of duty on May 1, 2011, we made a promise to "Never forget." We have not. Always in our thoughts and in our hearts. Thank you, sir, for your service.

Eric Godfrey

https://donorschoo.se/e/HlRjtjgUz2
I'm looking to get materials I need to create Escape Room type activities for next semester. Escape Room activities are rigorous and fun activities that require students to work together, use prior/learned knowledge, and think critically in order to solve puzzles and "beat the clock". These sort of activities are great for the curriculum but have the potential to reach outside the classroom as well. If you know of anyone looking to help out a teacher, send them my way! Thank you all!
